channel.title: Is my compile messed up? Please look
channel.description:
All the guides say it should look like this.
[code]@echo off COLOR 08 title YOURSERVERNAME Client "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin\java.exe" server pause[/code]
...mine looks like this,
[code]@echo off title TestScape Compiler javac *.java pause[/code]
Is there anything wrong?
TestScape Thanks -Ryu

item.title: Is my compile messed up? Please look
item.dc:creator: @bode bode
item.description:
@bode wrote:

Yeah change it… Also remember to do Start > Right Click My Computer > Advanced > Environment Variables > New

Variable Name: CLASSPATH
Variable Value: Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin;%CLASSPATH%;
